pr_title: Data source adapter for the Ethereum blockchain
pr_body:
_This PR has been created as part of the Google Summer of Code in the "Query the Blockchain" project._

I have created an adapter to query the Ethereum blockchain.

ref: [https://polypheny.org/community/gsoc/ideas/#query-the-blockchain](https://polypheny.org/community/gsoc/ideas/#query-the-blockchain)

This adapter creates 2 tables 
 - Transaction
 - Block
Both of them are queried in a running window fashion and the fetched data is shown in the table.

It uses the [Ethereum JSON-RPC API](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/apis/json-rpc/) to query the blockchain.
Since the blockchain is a stream of blocks that increases in realtime, it fetches the `n` latest blocks where n =  `Blocks` Parameter and then executes the query on these blocks.
